^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|The auction needs discussion. Everything through 2@S is routine. However, now that the auction has proceeded, pam's hand got a lot better.  5/5 hands are powerful, and since we have found a fit, it is likely her side has a fit as well.  3@D was very reasonable. A cue bid of a major, playing Michaels, shows the other major and an unspecified minor. However, there is another treatment you can use with your hand. Your other alternative would be 2N, which suggests both minors.|
PG| ***** 20 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|So, you might ask, how does that help, since you don't have both minors? If your partner understands, if des bids 3@C and you correct to 3@D, that shows diamonds and hearts. A similar treatment is when the auction goes something like 1S-P-4S-4N. The 4N ostensibly shows clubs and diamonds, but again with diamonds and hearts you can correct clubs to diamonds.|
PG| ***** 21 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|Now, should des bid 4@D.  I think not. pam is clearly just balancing and des has some defense, so I think pass is best.  I was very tempted to double, and in match points I would have. As to why I bid 3@S, I used my competitive bidding principles.  I know we have a 9 card fit, so I should bid to the 3 level. Given the law of total tricks, if des assumes we both have a 9 card fit, the most likely result is we are down 1 and so are they.|
PG| ***** 22 ***** |


NT||cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|As it turns out, they are down 2, and we make, so her bid is a wash, given I did not double. My partner should not bid 4. If I wanted to invite game, I would bid 3@H. 3@S is simply competing. Some people play a convention known as "maximal doubles" , where a double by me would show a game invitational hand. But I like to reserve that for a penalty double.  3H is a game force because you have to be able to bid 3@S to compete. therefore, to invite, you must make some other bid.|
PG| ***** 23 ***** |


NT|^B@2
MarDef: So, what does 3@H shows? Extra points? Another suit?|
PG| ***** 24 ***** |


cp|8|AT|
^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|In the absence of competition by pam, it would show heart cards, and ask ally to bid 4@S with a max and/or good heart fit. However, over 3@D, it is simply a game try, says nothing about hearts because I have no other way to invite. In a non-competitive auction, 3@S would be an invite, but in a competitive auction it is not.|
